<doc id="207027" wikidata="Q134974" url="?curid=207027" title="Northern krill">
<text>Northern krill (Meganyctiphanes norvegica) is a species of krill that lives in the North Atlantic Ocean. It is an important component of the zooplankton, providing food for whales, seals, fish and birds. (In the Southern Ocean, Antarctic krill &quot;Euphausia superba&quot; fills a similar role.) &quot;M. norvegica&quot; is the only species recognised in the genus Meganyctiphanes.

