====Geometric variance and covariance====

The logarithm of the geometric variance, ln(var&quot;GX&quot;), of a distribution with random variable &quot;X&quot; is the second moment of the logarithm of &quot;X&quot; centered on the geometric mean of &quot;X&quot;, ln(&quot;GX&quot;):

:formula_111

and therefore, the geometric variance is:

:formula_112

