The symmetric case &quot;α&quot; = &quot;β&quot; simplifies the characteristic function of the beta distribution to a Bessel function, since in the special case &quot;α&quot; + &quot;β&quot; = 2&quot;α&quot; the confluent hypergeometric function (of the first kind) reduces to a Bessel function (the modified Bessel function of the first kind formula_158 ) using Kummer&#x27;s second transformation as follows:

