to obtain:

:formula_301

Another alternative is to calculate the support interval range formula_298 based on the sample variance and the sample skewness. For this purpose one can solve, in terms of the range formula_298, the equation expressing the squared skewness in terms of the sample variance, and the sample size ν (see section titled &quot;Skewness&quot; and &quot;Alternative parametrizations, four parameters&quot;):

